column5: ~~~Got out Sunday with a buddy Paul, launched at Sibs winds seemed light when  we headed out, but came on fast, causing the lake to push  some large rollers at us, which were tight together, making it real hard to phish, the Scouts were tight to the wind blown shore, where all the bait was blown into. So we stayed out deep marking some phish, but not a lot, moved all the way around Georgina. with nothing to show, for the day but our smiles for just being on the water
Glad you got out even a skunk fishing is better than a day on the couch.   Art
